"{\"value\":{\"mdx\":\"# Verify SDK\\n\\nThe Verify SDK (`react-native-zcam1-verify`) validates the authenticity of C2PA-signed photos with embedded proofs.\\n\\n## Installation\\n\\n```bash\\nnpm i react-native-zcam1-verify\\ncd ios && pod install\\n```\\n\\n## Core Concepts\\n\\nThe Verify SDK:\\n- Extracts C2PA manifests from photos\\n- Verifies the photo hash matches the manifest\\n- Validates bindings (Apple App Attest signatures) for photos with `succinct.bindings`\\n- Validates ZK proofs against a pinned Apple Root CA for photos with `succinct.proof`\\n- Extracts capture metadata (device info, camera settings, etc.)\\n- Confirms the photo was taken on a genuine iOS device\\n\\n## API Reference\\n\\n### `VerifiableFile`\\n\\nClass for verifying photo authenticity.\\n\\n```tsx\\nimport { VerifiableFile } from \\\"react-native-zcam1-verify\\\";\\n\\nconst file = new VerifiableFile(photoUri);\\n```\\n\\n**Constructor:**\\n- `uriOrPath` - File path or URI to the photo\\n\\n### `VerifiableFile.verifyHash()`\\n\\nChecks that the photo's content hash matches the hash recorded in the C2PA manifest.\\n\\n```tsx\\nconst isHashValid: boolean = file.verifyHash();\\n```\\n\\n**Returns:** `true` if the file contents haven't been tampered with\\n\\n### `VerifiableFile.verifyBindings()`\\n\\nVerifies the Apple App Attest bindings for photos that have `succinct.bindings` but haven't been proven yet. This is useful for verifying photos before proof generation or when using bindings-only verification.\\n\\n```tsx\\nconst isBindingsValid: boolean = file.verifyBindings(appAttestProduction);\\n```\\n\\n**Parameters:**\\n- `appAttestProduction` - `true` if the photo was captured in production mode, `false` for development\\n\\n**Returns:** `true` if the bindings are valid\\n\\n**Note:** This method works for photos with `succinct.bindings`. For photos with `succinct.proof`, use `verifyProof()` instead.\\n\\n### `VerifiableFile.verifyProof()`\\n\\nValidates the embedded ZK proof against the photo hash and Apple Root CA.\\n\\n```tsx\\nconst isProofValid: boolean = file.verifyProof();\\n```\\n\\n**Returns:** `true` if the proof is valid\\n\\n**Throws:** Error if the photo doesn't contain a `succinct.proof` assertion\\n\\n### `VerifiableFile.dataHash()`\\n\\nReturns the file's content hash as recorded in the active C2PA manifest.\\n\\n```tsx\\nconst hash: string | undefined = file.dataHash();\\n```\\n\\n**Returns:** The manifest data hash (base64-encoded string), or `undefined` if not available\\n\\n### `VerifiableFile.captureMetadata()`\\n\\nReturns the capture metadata from the C2PA manifest, containing device info and camera settings recorded at capture time.\\n\\n```tsx\\nimport { CaptureMetadata } from \\\"react-native-zcam1-verify\\\";\\n\\nconst metadata: CaptureMetadata | null = file.captureMetadata();\\n```\\n\\n**Returns:** The capture metadata object, or `null` if not present\\n\\n**Metadata includes:**\\n- `action` - The capture action type\\n- `when` - Timestamp of capture\\n- `parameters` - Device and camera settings:\\n  - `device_make`, `device_model`\\n  - `software_version`\\n  - `x_resolution`, `y_resolution`\\n  - `orientation`\\n  - `iso`, `exposure_time`\\n  - `focal_length`, `depth_of_field`\\n\\n## Complete Example\\n\\n```tsx\\nimport { useState } from \\\"react\\\";\\nimport { View, Button, Text, StyleSheet } from \\\"react-native\\\";\\nimport { launchImageLibrary } from \\\"react-native-image-picker\\\";\\nimport { VerifiableFile } from \\\"react-native-zcam1-verify\\\";\\n\\ntype VerificationResult = {\\n  hashValid: boolean;\\n  proofValid: boolean;\\n  authentic: boolean;\\n};\\n\\nexport function VerifyScreen() {\\n  const [result, setResult] = useState<VerificationResult>();\\n  const [error, setError] = useState<string>();\\n\\n  const handlePickAndVerify = async () => {\\n    setResult(undefined);\\n    setError(undefined);\\n\\n    const response = await launchImageLibrary({\\n      mediaType: \\\"photo\\\",\\n      selectionLimit: 1,\\n    });\\n\\n    const asset = response.assets?.[0];\\n    if (!asset?.uri) return;\\n\\n    try {\\n      const file = new VerifiableFile(asset.uri);\\n\\n      const hashValid = file.verifyHash();\\n      const proofValid = file.verifyProof();\\n\\n      setResult({\\n        hashValid,\\n        proofValid,\\n        authentic: hashValid && proofValid,\\n      });\\n    } catch (err: any) {\\n      setError(err.message);\\n    }\\n  };\\n\\n  return (\\n    <View style={styles.container}>\\n      <Button title=\\\"Select Photo to Verify\\\" onPress={handlePickAndVerify} />\\n\\n      {result && (\\n        <View style={styles.result}>\\n          <Text style={styles.title}>\\n            {result.authentic ? \\\"✓ Authentic\\\" : \\\"✗ Not Authentic\\\"}\\n          </Text>\\n          <Text>Hash Valid: {result.hashValid ? \\\"Yes\\\" : \\\"No\\\"}</Text>\\n          <Text>Proof Valid: {result.proofValid ? \\\"Yes\\\" : \\\"No\\\"}</Text>\\n        </View>\\n      )}\\n\\n      {error && <Text style={styles.error}>Error: {error}</Text>}\\n    </View>\\n  );\\n}\\n\\nconst styles = StyleSheet.create({\\n  container: { flex: 1, padding: 16 },\\n  result: { marginTop: 24, padding: 16, backgroundColor: \\\"#f0f0f0\\\", borderRadius: 8 },\\n  title: { fontSize: 18, fontWeight: \\\"bold\\\", marginBottom: 8 },\\n  error: { marginTop: 16, color: \\\"red\\\" },\\n});\\n```\\n\\n## Verification Helper\\n\\nCreate a reusable verification function:\\n\\n```tsx\\nimport { VerifiableFile } from \\\"react-native-zcam1-verify\\\";\\n\\nexport type VerificationStatus =\\n  | { status: \\\"authentic\\\" }\\n  | { status: \\\"invalid_hash\\\" }\\n  | { status: \\\"invalid_proof\\\" }\\n  | { status: \\\"no_manifest\\\" }\\n  | { status: \\\"error\\\"; message: string };\\n\\nexport function verifyPhoto(uri: string): VerificationStatus {\\n  try {\\n    const file = new VerifiableFile(uri);\\n\\n    if (!file.verifyHash()) {\\n      return { status: \\\"invalid_hash\\\" };\\n    }\\n\\n    if (!file.verifyProof()) {\\n      return { status: \\\"invalid_proof\\\" };\\n    }\\n\\n    return { status: \\\"authentic\\\" };\\n  } catch (error: any) {\\n    if (error.message?.includes(\\\"no manifest\\\")) {\\n      return { status: \\\"no_manifest\\\" };\\n    }\\n    return { status: \\\"error\\\", message: error.message };\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## What Verification Checks\\n\\n| Check | What It Validates | Use Case |\\n|-------|-------------------|----------|\\n| `verifyHash()` | Photo bytes match the SHA-256 hash in the C2PA manifest | Always use this first to check file integrity |\\n| `verifyBindings()` | Apple App Attest signature is valid and corresponds to the photo hash | For photos with `succinct.bindings` (before proof generation) |\\n| `verifyProof()` | ZK proof is valid and chains to the Apple Root CA | For photos with `succinct.proof` (after proof generation) |\\n\\n**Verification Flow:**\\n\\nFor photos with `succinct.bindings`:\\n1. Call `verifyHash()` to check file integrity\\n2. Call `verifyBindings()` to verify the Apple App Attest signature\\n\\nFor photos with `succinct.proof`:\\n1. Call `verifyHash()` to check file integrity\\n2. Call `verifyProof()` to verify the ZK proof\\n\\nBoth hash and bindings/proof checks must pass for a photo to be considered authentic.\\n\\n## Notes\\n\\n- Verification is performed locally—no network required\\n- Use `verifyBindings()` for photos with `succinct.bindings` (before proof generation)\\n- Use `verifyProof()` for photos with `succinct.proof` (after proof generation)\\n- Photos with only `succinct.bindings` will fail `verifyProof()` (they haven't been proven yet)\\n- Photos with `succinct.proof` can use either verification method, but `verifyProof()` provides stronger guarantees\\n- The Apple Root CA is pinned in the SDK; proofs must chain to this root\\n- `captureMetadata()` provides access to device and camera settings recorded at capture time\\n\",\"document\":[{\"href\":\"/sdk/verify#verify-sdk\",\"html\":\"</header>\\n<p>The Verify SDK (<code>react-native-zcam1-verify</code>) validates the authenticity of C2PA-signed photos with embedded proofs.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/sdk/verify.mdx#verify-sdk\",\"isPage\":true,\"text\":\"\\nThe Verify SDK (react-native-zcam1-verify) validates the authenticity of C2PA-signed photos with embedded proofs.\\n\",\"title\":\"Verify SDK\",\"titles\":[]},{\"href\":\"/sdk/verify#installation\",\"html\":\"\\n<pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">npm</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> i</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> react-native-zcam1-verify</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">cd</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> ios</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> &amp;&amp; </span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">pod</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> install</span></span></code></pre>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/sdk/verify.mdx#installation\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nnpm i react-native-zcam1-verify\\ncd ios &amp;&amp; pod install\\n\",\"title\":\"Installation\",\"titles\":[\"Verify SDK\"]},{\"href\":\"/sdk/verify#core-concepts\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>The Verify SDK:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Extracts C2PA manifests from photos</li>\\n<li>Verifies the photo hash matches the manifest</li>\\n<li>Validates bindings (Apple App Attest signatures) for photos with <code>succinct.bindings</code></li>\\n<li>Validates ZK proofs against a pinned Apple Root CA for photos with <code>succinct.proof</code></li>\\n<li>Extracts capture metadata (device info, camera settings, etc.)</li>\\n<li>Confirms the photo was taken on a genuine iOS device</li>\\n</ul>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/sdk/verify.mdx#core-concepts\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nThe Verify SDK:\\n\\nExtracts C2PA manifests from photos\\nVerifies the photo hash matches the manifest\\nValidates bindings (Apple App Attest signatures) for photos with succinct.bindings\\nValidates ZK proofs against a pinned Apple Root CA for photos with succinct.proof\\nExtracts capture metadata (device info, camera settings, etc.)\\nConfirms the photo was taken on a genuine iOS device\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"Core Concepts\",\"titles\":[\"Verify SDK\"]},{\"href\":\"/sdk/verify#api-reference\",\"html\":\"\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/sdk/verify.mdx#api-reference\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\n\",\"title\":\"API Reference\",\"titles\":[\"Verify SDK\"]},{\"href\":\"/sdk/verify#verifiablefile\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Class for verifying photo authenticity.</p>\\n<pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\" data-empty-line=\\\"true\\\"> </span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\" data-empty-line=\\\"true\\\"> </span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">const</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> file</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> =</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> new</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\"> VerifiableFile</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(photoUri);</span></span></code></pre>\\n<strong>Constructor:</strong>\\n<ul>\\n<li><code>uriOrPath</code> - File path or URI to the photo</li>\\n</ul>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/sdk/verify.mdx#verifiablefile\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nClass for verifying photo authenticity.\\n \\n \\nconst file = new VerifiableFile(photoUri);\\nConstructor:\\n\\nuriOrPath - File path or URI to the photo\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"VerifiableFile\",\"titles\":[\"Verify SDK\",\"API Reference\"]},{\"href\":\"/sdk/verify#verifiablefileverifyhash\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Checks that the photo&#x27;s content hash matches the hash recorded in the C2PA manifest.</p>\\n<pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">const</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> isHashValid</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">:</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> boolean</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> =</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> file.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">verifyHash</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">();</span></span></code></pre>\\n<p><strong>Returns:</strong> <code>true</code> if the file contents haven&#x27;t been tampered with</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/sdk/verify.mdx#verifiablefileverifyhash\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nChecks that the photo&#x27;s content hash matches the hash recorded in the C2PA manifest.\\nconst isHashValid: boolean = file.verifyHash();\\nReturns: true if the file contents haven&#x27;t been tampered with\\n\",\"title\":\"VerifiableFile.verifyHash()\",\"titles\":[\"Verify SDK\",\"API Reference\"]},{\"href\":\"/sdk/verify#verifiablefileverifybindings\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Verifies the Apple App Attest bindings for photos that have <code>succinct.bindings</code> but haven&#x27;t been proven yet. This is useful for verifying photos before proof generation or when using bindings-only verification.</p>\\n<pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">const</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> isBindingsValid</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">:</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> boolean</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> =</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> file.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">verifyBindings</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(appAttestProduction);</span></span></code></pre>\\n<strong>Parameters:</strong>\\n<ul>\\n<li><code>appAttestProduction</code> - <code>true</code> if the photo was captured in production mode, <code>false</code> for development</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p><strong>Returns:</strong> <code>true</code> if the bindings are valid</p>\\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> This method works for photos with <code>succinct.bindings</code>. For photos with <code>succinct.proof</code>, use <code>verifyProof()</code> instead.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/sdk/verify.mdx#verifiablefileverifybindings\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nVerifies the Apple App Attest bindings for photos that have succinct.bindings but haven&#x27;t been proven yet. This is useful for verifying photos before proof generation or when using bindings-only verification.\\nconst isBindingsValid: boolean = file.verifyBindings(appAttestProduction);\\nParameters:\\n\\nappAttestProduction - true if the photo was captured in production mode, false for development\\n\\nReturns: true if the bindings are valid\\nNote: This method works for photos with succinct.bindings. For photos with succinct.proof, use verifyProof() instead.\\n\",\"title\":\"VerifiableFile.verifyBindings()\",\"titles\":[\"Verify SDK\",\"API Reference\"]},{\"href\":\"/sdk/verify#verifiablefileverifyproof\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Validates the embedded ZK proof against the photo hash and Apple Root CA.</p>\\n<pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">const</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> isProofValid</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">:</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> boolean</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> =</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> file.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">verifyProof</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">();</span></span></code></pre>\\n<p><strong>Returns:</strong> <code>true</code> if the proof is valid</p>\\n<p><strong>Throws:</strong> Error if the photo doesn&#x27;t contain a <code>succinct.proof</code> assertion</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/sdk/verify.mdx#verifiablefileverifyproof\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nValidates the embedded ZK proof against the photo hash and Apple Root CA.\\nconst isProofValid: boolean = file.verifyProof();\\nReturns: true if the proof is valid\\nThrows: Error if the photo doesn&#x27;t contain a succinct.proof assertion\\n\",\"title\":\"VerifiableFile.verifyProof()\",\"titles\":[\"Verify SDK\",\"API Reference\"]},{\"href\":\"/sdk/verify#verifiablefiledatahash\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Returns the file&#x27;s content hash as recorded in the active C2PA manifest.</p>\\n<pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">const</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> hash</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">:</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> string</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> |</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> undefined</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> =</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> file.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">dataHash</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">();</span></span></code></pre>\\n<p><strong>Returns:</strong> The manifest data hash (base64-encoded string), or <code>undefined</code> if not available</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/sdk/verify.mdx#verifiablefiledatahash\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nReturns the file&#x27;s content hash as recorded in the active C2PA manifest.\\nconst hash: string | undefined = file.dataHash();\\nReturns: The manifest data hash (base64-encoded string), or undefined if not available\\n\",\"title\":\"VerifiableFile.dataHash()\",\"titles\":[\"Verify SDK\",\"API Reference\"]},{\"href\":\"/sdk/verify#verifiablefilecapturemetadata\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Returns the capture metadata from the C2PA manifest, containing device info and camera settings recorded at capture time.</p>\\n<pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\" data-empty-line=\\\"true\\\"> </span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\" data-empty-line=\\\"true\\\"> </span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">const</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> metadata</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">:</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\"> CaptureMetadata</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> |</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> null</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> =</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> file.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">captureMetadata</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">();</span></span></code></pre>\\n<p><strong>Returns:</strong> The capture metadata object, or <code>null</code> if not present</p>\\n<strong>Metadata includes:</strong>\\n<ul>\\n<li><code>action</code> - The capture action type</li>\\n<li><code>when</code> - Timestamp of capture</li>\\n<li><code>parameters</code> - Device and camera settings:\\n<ul>\\n<li><code>device_make</code>, <code>device_model</code></li>\\n<li><code>software_version</code></li>\\n<li><code>x_resolution</code>, <code>y_resolution</code></li>\\n<li><code>orientation</code></li>\\n<li><code>iso</code>, <code>exposure_time</code></li>\\n<li><code>focal_length</code>, <code>depth_of_field</code></li>\\n</ul>\\n</li>\\n</ul>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/sdk/verify.mdx#verifiablefilecapturemetadata\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nReturns the capture metadata from the C2PA manifest, containing device info and camera settings recorded at capture time.\\n \\n \\nconst metadata: CaptureMetadata | null = file.captureMetadata();\\nReturns: The capture metadata object, or null if not present\\nMetadata includes:\\n\\naction - The capture action type\\nwhen - Timestamp of capture\\nparameters - Device and camera settings:\\n\\ndevice_make, device_model\\nsoftware_version\\nx_resolution, y_resolution\\norientation\\niso, exposure_time\\nfocal_length, depth_of_field\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"VerifiableFile.captureMetadata()\",\"titles\":[\"Verify SDK\",\"API Reference\"]},{\"href\":\"/sdk/verify#complete-example\",\"html\":\"\\n<pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"l